      "span_text": "Two independent lineages of transgenic mice (designated T1 and T3 mice) were generated that expressed HLA-G under the control of promoter elements derived from the murine H-2K b gene. Previously, we reported that HLA-G expression occurs on most, if not all, cell types tested in HLA-G mice, and demonstrated that HLA-G behaves as a major transplantation antigen and restriction element for peptide presentation in mice [CITATION_1] ."
